fields.description:
Issue reporter can schedule issue (set fix version) if he has _Edit Issues_ permission. He should only be allowed to set fix version if he has _Resolve Issues_, which says _"Ability to resolve and reopen issues. This includes the ability to set a fix version."_

The steps to reproduce this:
# Create a new user;
# Login into JIRA using the user created in the step 1;
# Create an issue;
# Now click on Go To Planning Board (in the left panel);
# Wait while the Planning Board is open;
# Now drag and drop the selected issue to a version available;
# Check the issue details for the field "Fix-For Version(s)".

Kind regards,
Dushan
